item.title: Delta flight diverts to New York after passengers are served spoiled food

item.title: Hurricane Beryl kills at least 7 as it batters the Caribbean
item.description: Hurricane Beryl continues to tear through the Caribbean bringing dangerous waves and ferocious winds as a Category 4 storm. The violent system arrives as more than 105 million Americans brace for what could be a record-breaking Forth of July heat wave. NBC’s Sam Brock reports from Jamaica and TODAY’s Dylan Dreyer tracks the latest forecast.
